    "content_hash": "a5206997cfd3562f",
    "department": "Sales",
    "description": "ABOUT JUICEBOX\n\nJuicebox is on a mission to help teams win the talent war.\n\nIn the age of AI, human ingenuity is the ultimate scarce resource. Recruiting is a zero-sum game where you either compete or lose.\n\nTeams at Ramp, Notion, and leading AI labs use Juicebox to power their hiring, alongside 5,000+ customers from early-stage startups to Fortune 500 companies.\n\nWe are on the path to $100M in ARR with 20%+ monthly growth, powering thousands of searches every day and making Juicebox one of the fastest-growing AI SaaS companies in the world.\n\nJuicebox has raised over $116M in funding from lead investors including Sequoia Capital, DST Global, and NFDG. Read more about our $80M Series B https://juicebox.ai/blog/series-b here. Additional investors in Juicebox include Y Combinator, Coatue, Bond, Lux, Verified Capital, and Committed Capital.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re hiring a Sales Development Representative to join our growing sales team and fuel Juicebox’s next stage of growth.\n\nYou’ll own top-of-funnel pipeline generation - crafting strategic outbound outreach to Heads of Talent, VP People, and recruiting agency owners.\n\nThis isn’t a cookie-cutter SDR role. You’ll:\n\n - Partner closely with AEs, Product, and Marketing to engage prospects\n\n - Help refine our outbound playbook alongside our AEs\n\n - Get in early on a company that’s 10x’d revenue in the last 12 months and has more demand than we can handle\n\nWe’re seeing strong pull from both in-house TA teams and recruiting agencies — and many of our 2,000+ customers are ready for expansion.\n\nIf you're looking for a high-leverage role at a product-first company with real traction, this is it.\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE IS DIFFERENT\n\n - Career upside: Clear paths into AE or SDR Management roles within 12 months\n\n - Strategic buyers: You’ll connect with Heads of TA, VP People, and agency owners\n\n - Shape the playbook: Help build our outbound strategy from scratch\n\n\nYOU’RE A FIT IF YOU…\n\n - Have 1+ years of sales or customer-facing experience (SaaS or startup is a plus)\n\n - Are a strong communicator: clear, concise, and persuasive\n\n - Thrive in a fast-paced, founder-led GTM environment\n\n - Love testing new strategies and learning from the data\n\n - Have experience with CRMs (HubSpot, Salesforce) and prospecting tools (Apollo, Clay)\n\n - Are located in or willing to relocate to San Francisco (in-office 5 days a week required)\n\n\nNICE TO HAVE\n\n - Experience selling to TA / HR personas\n\n - Experience at an early-stage startup or GTM team \u003c5\n\n - Comfortable navigating Product-Led Growth environments (e.g., free sign-ups, trials)\n\n\nCOMPENSATION \u0026 BENEFITS\n\n - $70K–$90K base salary, based on experience\n\n - $110 - $130K OTE\n\n - Uncapped commission, driven through qualified meetings booked quota\n\n - Generous benefits, including medical, dental, and vision\n\n - Lunch stipend",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
